{\b Overview}\par
Comprehensive analysis of major trading strategies for educational purposes. This document serves as a reference for understanding different approaches to market analysis and investment decisions.\par
\par
{\b Major Trading Strategy Categories}\par
\par
{\b 1. Fundamental Analysis}\par
{\b Core Principle:} Company/asset intrinsic value analysis\par
{\b -} P/E Ratios - Price-to-earnings analysis\par
{\b -} DCF Models - Discounted cash flow valuation\par
{\b -} Financial Statement Analysis - Balance sheet, income statement review\par
{\b -} Industry Analysis - Sector trends and competitive positioning\par
{\b -} Economic Indicators - GDP, inflation, interest rates impact\par
\par
{\b Pros:} Long-term value identification, less market noise sensitivity\par
{\b Cons:} Time-intensive research, slower reaction to market changes\par
\par
{\b 2. Technical Analysis}\par
{\b Core Principle:} Price action and volume pattern analysis\par
{\b -} Chart Patterns - Head & shoulders, triangles, support/resistance\par
{\b -} Moving Averages - SMA, EMA crossover strategies\par
{\b -} Momentum Indicators - RSI, MACD, Stochastic oscillators\par
{\b -} Volume Analysis - Trading volume confirmation signals\par
{\b -} Fibonacci Retracements - Support/resistance level identification\par
\par
{\b Pros:} Quick decision-making, works across timeframes\par
{\b Cons:} Can generate false signals, historical patterns may not repeat\par
\par
{\b 3. Quantitative Strategies}\par
{\b Core Principle:} Mathematical models and statistical analysis\par
{\b -} Mean Reversion - Asset prices return to historical averages\par
{\b -} Momentum Strategies - Trend-following based on price velocity\par
{\b -} Pairs Trading - Market-neutral positions in correlated assets\par
{\b -} Statistical Arbitrage - Exploiting pricing inefficiencies\par
{\b -} Factor Investing - Value, growth, quality, momentum factors\par
\par
{\b Implementation Considerations}\par
\par
{\b Technology Requirements}\par
{\b -} Data Sources - Real-time and historical market data\par
{\b -} Analysis Tools - Charting software, statistical packages\par
{\b -} Execution Platforms - API access, latency considerations\par
{\b -} Risk Systems - Real-time monitoring, automated alerts\par
\par
